wikipedia_page.main: Bob Starkey (8 January 1904 – 19 April 1978) was a British rower. He competed in the men's coxed four event at the 1928 Summer Olympics.

response: Bob Starkey (born September 7, 1959) is an assistant coach for the Auburn Tigers women's basketball team as of April 15, 2021. He served as an assistant under head coach Gary Blair at Texas A&M from 2012 to 2021.
